<h1>Levitating magnet brings space physics to fusion</h1>
<div class="dek">Tests on a machine that mimics a planet’s magnetic field show that it may offer an ‘alternative path’ to taming nuclear fusion for power generation.</div>
<div class="byline">David L. Chandler, MIT News Office<br /></div></div>
        <div class="clear"></div>
        <div id="scol1">
<div class="section">
<h2>today's news</h2><div class="story"><div class="external_byline_a1" style="margin-top:5px;">THE MULTICORE FUTURE, PART 4</div><h3><a href="/newsoffice/2011/multicore-series-4-0228.html">No backtalk</a></h3><div class="storypic"><a href="/newsoffice/2011/multicore-series-4-0228.html"><img src="http://img.mit.edu/newsoffice/images/article_images/tn/20110225174323-1.jpg" alt="" height="124" width="180" /></a><br /><div class="caption"><span class="credit">Graphic: Christine Daniloff</span></div></div><p>One key to making parallel algorithms efficient is to minimize the amount of communication between cores.  </p></div><h4><a href="/newsoffice/2011/multicore-series-3-0225.html">Retooling algorithms</a></h4><div class="smdate">February 25, 2011</div><h4><a href="/newsoffice/2011/multicore-series-2-0224.html">The next operating system</a></h4><div class="smdate">February 24, 2011</div><h4><a href="/newsoffice/2011/multicore-series-1-0223.html">Designing the hardware</a></h4><div class="smdate">February 23, 2011</div><h4><a href="/newsoffice/2011/itw-green-grease-0224.html">In The World: Turning old oil into new mileage</a></h4><div class="smdate">February 24, 2011</div><h4><a href="/newsoffice/2011/wilkerson-event-0224.html">A migration that shaped a nation</a></h4><div class="smdate">February 24, 2011</div><h4><a href="/newsoffice/2011/nano-sized-vaccines-0222.html">Nano-sized vaccines</a></h4><div class="smdate">February 22, 2011</div></div>
</div>
        <div id="scol2">
            <div id="main_container"><div class="storyfull">
	<div class="lead">
					<div class="storypic">
            					
                <img src="http://web.mit.edu/newsoffice//images/article_images/20100122123044-1.jpg" width="368" height="252" alt="" />
									<div class="caption">
													The Levitated Dipole Experiment (LDX) reactor is housed inside a 16-foot-diameter steel structure in a building on the MIT campus that also houses MIT’s other fusion reactor, a tokamak called Alcator C-mod.															<br />
																										<span class="credit">Photo courtesy of the LDX team</span>
											</div>
				                
                                
			</div>
				<div class="leadwithimage">
			<div class="byline">
									<div class="date">January 25, 2010</div>
							</div>
			<br />
			<div class="storybuttons">
